Sure! To add the paste and image/file buttons to the top-right corner of the input box, we can modify the existing layout slightly. Here’s how you could do it:

1. **Prevent the default behavior**: We'll remove the `default` parameter from the `button` method to prevent the default action from occurring.
2. **Add the button styles**: We'll apply CSS to make the buttons more visually prominent and aligned correctly.

Here's the updated code:

```rust
use std::fmt;
use html5ever::prettify;

#[derive(Debug)]
pub struct Button {
    pub type_: String,
    pub text: String,
}

impl fmt::Display for Button {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter) -> fmt::Result {
        match self.type_ {
            "text" => write!(f, "{}", self.text),
            _ => return fmt::Display::fmt(&self.text, f),
        }
    }
}

impl From<String> for Button {
    fn from(type_: String, text: String) -> Self {
        Button { type_, text }
    }
}

/// Create a new instance of [Button]
fn create_button(type_: String, text: String) -> impl fmt::Display + From<String> {
    Button { type_, text }
}

/// Apply style to the button
fn style(button: &Button) {
    button.type_.to_string().prettify(&std::io::stderr());
}

/// Add the paste and image/file buttons to the top-right corner of the input box
fn add_buttons_to_input_box() -> impl fmt::Display + From<String> {
    let mut input_box = html5ever::InputBoxBuilder::new()
        .with_label("Paste")
        .add_text_field("Type your text here...")
        .add_button("Image/Upload")
        .add_button("File/Upload")
        .build();

    input_box.add_css_class("top_right");
    input_box
}
```

### Explanation:

1. **`create_button` method**: Creates a new `Button` object with a default value.
2. **`style` function**: Formats the button's text using `prettify`.
3. **`add_buttons_to_input_box` function**: Adds a CSS class `.top_right` to the `input_box`. This ensures that the buttons appear in the top-right corner of the input box.

This way, you can easily replace "type_" with whatever you want, and the buttons will be styled accordingly.

